cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CR, cs.IR 

This paper deals with abnormal event detection from trajectory data using deep neural networks and adversarial learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a new adversarial approach for building a binary classifier, which involves training a discriminator to distinguish normal and abnormal trajectory reconstruction errors given by a deep autoencoder. This suggests that the paper could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also deals with detecting abnormal events, which could fall under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
